<chapter><title>Quick start guide</title>

<sect1><title>Foo</title>
  <para>
    Follow the instructions in the installation section of this user manual and then at a shell prompt, type
</para>
<programlisting>
./gdms
</programlisting>
<para>
  To open a data set, select <command>File</command> - <command>Open</command>. Browse to the location in which the
  data sets to be opened resides and then click <command>Open</command>.
</para>

<para>
  Now that a dataset has been loaded, use the <command>Maths</command> menu to carry out data processing. For further details of specific
  options here, please refer to the Reference chapter. 
</para>
<para>
  To close the data set currently in focus, select
  <command>File</command> - <command>Close.</command>.
</para>
<para>
  To exit the program, simply select <command>File</command> -
  <command>Exit</command>. 
</para>
<para>
  To save the data set after processing, select <command>File</command> -
  <command>Save</command>. Choose the desired location and click <command>OK</command>.
</para>
<para>
  To save under a
  different file name, select <command>File</command> - <command>Save As</command>. Enter a file name and once again,
  choose a location and click <command>OK</command>.
</para>
</sect1>

</chapter>
